From d4fbff2fb73694e66d997c78072eee83ba2047c0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: therockbot <therockbot@amd.com>
Date: Tue, 12 May 2026 23:32:06 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Suppress -Wlifetime-safety compiler errors

The amd-staging compiler introduces -Wlifetime-safety-lifetimebound-violation
and -Wlifetime-safety-intra-tu-suggestions warnings. Combined with -Werror in
Composable Kernel, this causes build failures in tuple.hpp, buffer_view.hpp,
kernel_launch.hpp, and device_grouped_conv_fwd_multiple_abd_xdl_cshuffle.hpp.

Suppress both warnings in the affected headers, and add
-Wno-unknown-warning-option to avoid warnings on compilers that do not
recognize these options yet.

Upstream fix: https://github.com/ROCm/rocm-libraries/pull/7384
